Shell Scripting Task-1

1- Ask the user to enter the path of a directory to back up.

2-Check if the directory exists.

3-If the directory does not exist, print an error message and exit.

4- Ask the user to enter a name for the backup file.

5-Create a compressed backup of the directory into a tar and gz.

6-Check if the backup was created successfully.

7- If the backup was successful, print a success message; otherwise, print an error message and exit.

8-Ask the user to enter a file path to check permissions.

9-Check if the file exists.

10-If the file does not exist, print an error message and exit.

11-Display the permissions of the file in a readable format.
